## Concern C — Symmetric event-listener for shriek FX

**Verdict:** PASS — structural refactor, behavior identical.
**Commit:** `65faaf9bd1`

Moved the `HuntFX.burst` + `flashScreen` calls out of `hunt-enemies.js`'s
AI tick into a `WG.Engine.on('enemy:shriek', …)` subscriber in
`hunt-fx.js`, mirroring the existing `repair:complete` pattern. The
subscriber reads tunables from `creature._typeData.shriek*` /
`creature._typeData.accent`, so designer edits to the catalog flow
through without touching the FX module.

Per the worker spec, `addTrauma` stays inline in the AI tick (kept
tightly coupled to the shriek's timing). Trauma 0.3, particle count 16,
flash `#a060ff` @ 0.3 alpha / 200 ms — all equivalent to pre-refactor
state.

## Concern D — `wg-rift-intrude` wired to procedural canvas

**Verdict:** PASS — rift visual canon is now testable on the procedural
canvas. **Visual test passed.** **Commit:** `934a9278f9`

Added `RIFT_GUESTS = []` array in `js/wg-game.js`. When the active
character id is in the array, `renderHero()` adds the
`.wg-rift-intrude` class to the procedural character canvas AND
switches its centering from `transform:translateX(-50%)` to
`left:calc(50% - 48px)` — required because the `wgRiftGlitch`
keyframe owns the `transform` property (per the comment on the CSS
rule in `index.html:74-80`).

**Test path executed:**
1. Set `RIFT_GUESTS = ['lantern_acolyte']`.
2. Loaded http://localhost:3996/ via Claude Preview.
3. Confirmed via `preview_eval`:
   - `activeId` is `lantern_acolyte`.
   - The character canvas (96×140 css, z-index 2) carries the
     `wg-rift-intrude` class.
   - Inline style is `position: absolute; left: calc(50% - 48px);
     bottom: 18%; width: 96px; height: 140px; …` (no `transform` —
     keyframe-safe).
4. Reverted `RIFT_GUESTS` to `[]`.
5. Reloaded; confirmed via `preview_eval` that the class is gone and
   centering is back to `left:50%; transform:translateX(-50%);`.

`RIFT_GUESTS` ships empty — no rift class applied to anything — so
shipped behavior is unchanged. The wiring is in place for the first
real rift guest (Ysabel, queued behind KingshotPro launch) to flip
the array.

